I have zero idea why. I was reading John Scott Haldane (from the Haldane effect)'s lectures from 1930 and he explains how only a fool would think CO2 is not important and how too little is just as bad as too much, etc... For some reason a literal century later everyone is dumber.

If you've talked to a physiology professor or students, one of the things you will notice is they are bizarrely autistic about CO2 being a "waste product", other topics they are open-minded about, you can have a conversation with them, but this one turns them into massive retards

You can find it online. "J. S. Haldane, The Philosophical Basis of Biology: Donnellan Lectures, University of Dublin, 1930, Hodder and Stoughton Limited (1931)." Takes a few hours to read. He talks about how CO2 is important and serves a regulating role. From 100 years (!!!) ago.
